  "text": "Since α-synuclein null mice do not display any striking phenotype (our observation; [CITATION_1] ) expression of β-synuclein was analyzed for possible compensatory mechanisms. Western blot analysis revealed that protein levels of β-synuclein remain unaffected by the α-synuclein deletion at any stage of postnatal development (Fig. 3A) . Expression of the 19 kDa protein was uniform in the 129/ Ola, ICR, and the BL6JHUK strain and increased noticeably during postnatal development.",
